Listen, my love.
I tried. God knows I tried with everything in me to hold us together, to nurture what we had. I gave you my love in its rawest, purest form, hoping it would be enough to bridge the gaps that kept growing between us. But love, no matter how deep, canât fill a space where effort is missing on the other side. I fought for us until I had nothing left to give, and still, it wasnât enough to fix what we kept breaking. So now, Iâm stepping backânot because I want to, but because I have to. For both of us. My love, which was meant to be your sanctuary, became your burden. Maybe my absence will offer the peace my presence couldnât.

Let it be. Let it hurt, because itâs supposed to. Let it heal, because it must. And then, let it go. I donât hate you, but I canât keep loving you at the cost of losing myself. Itâs not easy to stop caring for someone who once meant the world, but Iâve realized love isnât enough if it isnât met with the same. I deserved more than empty promises and moments where I felt like I was the only one fighting. Maybe one day, youâll look back and see how much I poured into us, how all I wanted was to be loved the way I loved you. Maybe then youâll understand why I had to walk awayânot to hurt you, but to save myself.

So this is my goodbye, a quiet one wrapped in hope. Hopefully, youâll realize one day how much I loved youâhow deeply, how genuinely. Hopefully, youâll see that all I ever craved was your love and care, not perfection, just presence. Hopefully, youâll miss me, not as a person you lost, but as the one who truly saw you, loved you, and stayed far longer than most would have. And hopefully, when that day comes, it wonât be filled with regret, but with gratitude for what we shared. Until then, I wish you peace, even if itâs without me.
